    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">range_succ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `List.sum_append` is already a `simp` lemma</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>is pretty much the only comment I have on your code; that's a fine time to use <code>simp</code>. As for the gnarly bit at the end, it's hard to get automation to help you because your goal has this <code>Nat.div</code> in it, I think in your case I would have bashed it out like you did. Great effort getting it out by the way!</p>",
